plate was fried chicken sauce and rice. The Yakisoba plate was a mixture of noodles with vegetables like broccoli cabbage and carrots. The chicken was tasteful and had a hint of char to it which was great. The shrimp on the other hand was chewy and was very very over cooked I felt as if I was chewing on a rubber eraser. The eggroll was great and the shrimp tempura was delicious.  Definitely was a great experience and will be making a prompt return. I will probably say "NAY" to the shrimp though.
