4 Great for a quick lunch spot that's filling, relatively healthy, and not fast food at all. They have no-carb and low-carb options, when I'm actually being healthful, and they have the best goddamn Crab Rangoons in the city. I could eat those by the bucket.  My go-to meal is the katsu bowl with white rice and veggies, and it's pretty much chicken, rice, and veggies in equal portion. Let me reiterate that. It's a bowl, and it's not 80% rice. 33% chicken, 33% rice, 33% vegetable. Mind. Blown.   The people are always friendly, and the service is fast, which makes it a perfect spot for a comfortable lunch. Take out and Eat in both cause equally few problems, and I can usually eat for under $10.  Pros; - Good food, good folk, good pace, good prices.  - Crab Rangoons, holy shit, crab rangoons.  Cons:  - There's not one in spring Valley.  - For eat in, the restaurant is pretty darn small.
